  "body": "According to #3399 and #3465 React uses <code>escapeTextContentForBrowser</code> to replace \" with <code>&quot;</code> etc. This behavior is sane and awesome!\n\nProblem is that it also happens inside <code><style></code> tags, which is not so great. Turns things like <code>url(\"yolo.png\")</code> into <code>url(&quot;yolo.png&quot;)</code> which of course breaks.\n\nIt works fine if applied using `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`.\n",
